changes.description: Added aria-label attribute to IconButton component
changes.new_value: <IconButton onClick={() => navigate('/projects')} size="small" aria-label="Back to projects">

patterns_discovered.description: Adding descriptive aria-label attributes to icon-only buttons for screen reader support
Single-line modification targeting specific accessibility requirement without refactoring

gotchas_discovered.description: IconButton components that only contain icons (ArrowBackIcon) without visible text need aria-label to communicate their purpose to screen reader users
gotchas_discovered.mitigation: Always include aria-label on icon-only interactive elements in Material-UI

approach_outcome.testing_impact: No test changes required - accessibility attribute addition

recommendations.recommendation: Conduct full audit of other icon-only buttons throughout the application for missing aria-labels
recommendations.rationale: Pattern suggests potential similar accessibility gaps in other components

recommendations.recommendation: Establish linting rule or component wrapper to enforce aria-label on icon-only buttons
recommendations.rationale: Prevents recurrence of this type of accessibility oversight

recommendations.recommendation: Document accessibility requirements for different Material-UI components in component guidelines
recommendations.rationale: Helps team maintain consistent accessibility practices
